# Meme Generator Tasks

- [/] Project Setup
  - [ ] Create project directory (`python-meme-generator`)
  - [ ] Initialize Python virtual environment
  - [ ] Install dependencies (`flask`, `requests`, `pillow`)
- [ ] Backend (Flask)
  - [ ] Create `app.py`
  - [ ] Set up route to serve the main page
  - [ ] Set up API route to fetch memes from Imgflip
  - [ ] (Optional) Set up route to generate downloadable image
- [ ] Frontend Structure & Styling
  - [ ] Create `templates/index.html`
  - [ ] Create `static/style.css` implementing a "natural color" palette (earthy tones, off-whites, soft greens/browns) with a premium feel
  - [ ] Build the UI layout (Header, Meme Editor Canvas, Controls, Gallery)
- [ ] Frontend Logic
  - [ ] Create `static/script.js`
  - [ ] Fetch and display templates from the backend
  - [ ] Handle text inputs and update the meme preview live
- [ ] Verification
  - [ ] Run Flask server and test functionality
